# 🎓 University System — SQL Project

A beginner-to-intermediate SQL project that models a university database from scratch.  
Built as part of my **Data Science & Machine Learning journey** to strengthen my SQL foundations.

---

## 📌 About This Project

This project designs and queries a relational database for a university system. It covers everything from schema design and data insertion to joins, subqueries, views, and aggregate functions — all written in **MySQL**.

---

## 🗂️ Database Schema

The database `University_System` contains **6 tables**:

| Table | Description |
|---|---|
| `Department` | University departments (CS, SE, IT, etc.) |
| `Student` | Student records with CGPA and semester info |
| `Teacher` | Teacher records with specialization |
| `Courses` | Courses offered by each department |
| `Enrollment` | Student–course enrollment with grades |
| `Attendance` | Daily attendance records per student per course |

### Entity Relationships

```
Department
   ├── Student        (dep_ID → dep_ID)
   ├── Teacher        (dep_ID → dep_ID)
   └── Courses        (dep_ID → dep_ID)
          ├── Enrollment  (course_ID → course_ID)
          └── Attendance  (course_ID → course_ID)

Student
   ├── Enrollment  (student_id → student_id)
   └── Attendance  (student_id → student_id)
```

